The paper focuses on the persistence and availability of web resources referenced from papers in scholarly repositories, which is a topic that falls under the digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the study involves analyzing the metadata of the repositories and considering the results by discipline, which could fall under the categories of cryptography (cs.CR), cybernetics (cs.CY), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
